  "title": "Project Manager (School Laboratories, Facilities, Engineering)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Plan, manage, and deliver laboratories, engineering workshops, and facilities projects from concept to completion.</li><li>Oversee the development, upgrading, and operation of teaching and applied engineering laboratories and workshops.</li><li>Coordinate installation, testing, and commissioning of engineering and laboratory equipment.</li><li>Ensure reliability and safety of engineering systems supporting labs and facilities.</li><li>Oversee maintenance and improvement of buildings, classrooms, workshops, and common areas.</li><li>Manage contractors,consultants, and service providers.</li><li>Ensure compliance with environmental, fire safety, and hazardous materials regulations.</li><li>Work closely with academic staff to align facilities and laboratories with teaching and learning needs.</li><li>Lead and supervise technical staff, lab technologists, and facilities personnel.</li><li>Provide technical guidance and support staff development.</li><li>Contribute to long-term planning for laboratories, engineering facilities, and campus infrastructure.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Engineering, Project Management, or Facilities Management preferred.</li><li>Minimum 6 to 8 years’ experience in project management, facilities management, or engineering operations.</li><li>Proven experience managing <strong>laboratories, engineering workshops, or technical facilities</strong>, preferably in <strong>higher education environment.</strong></li><li>Experience working with <strong>contractors, consultants, and vendors</strong>.</li><li>Strong knowledge of <strong>engineering systems</strong> </li></ul>",
